What is Authentication and why required
● Process of recognizing a user’s identity.
● Process of giving individuals access to
system resources based on their identity.
● Protect system from unauthenticated user
© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Difference between three
● Identification:- Identification is the ability to identify
uniquely a user of a system
● Authentication:- Confirms your identity to grant
access to the system.
● Authorization:- Process of verifying type of access or
grant is allowed or not on a resource
© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Types of authentication
● Oauth (Open Authorization)
● Other ways like UN/PWD, SAML and LDAP
● Using authentication in request header
○ Username/password
○ Token
© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
What is Passport and types of strategies
● Passport:- Passport is authentication middleware for
Node
● Types of strategies
○ Local strategy
○ OAuth
○ JWT strategy
© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
What is JSON Web token
A JSON Web Token (JWT) is a JSON object that
is defined as a safe way to represent a set of
information between two parties. The token is
composed of a header, a payload, and a
signature.
© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.

© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
JWT backend token process
● Create the HEADER
● Create the PAYLOAD
● Create the SIGNATURE
● Put All Three JWT Components Together
● Send generated token to client side
● Get token and verify

What is Authorization and how applied
● Process to check user is authorised to access
a resource of not
● By applying RBAC (Role-based access
control), authorization can be implemented
© NIIT-StackRoute 2017-18.
Protecting node.js server from attacks
● Types of attacks
○ Session hijacking
○ Phishing
○ others
● Helmetjs can help to protect your app from
some well-known web vulnerabilities by
setting HTTP headers appropriately.
